## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The key is to **inject** the current trace context into RabbitMQ message headers on publish, and **extract** it on consume to create a linked span.

### Service A — Publisher

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;
using RabbitMQ.Client;

private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceA.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void PublishOrder(IModel channel, byte[] body)
{
    using var activity = Source.StartActivity("OrderEvent send", ActivityKind.Producer);

    var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
    props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

    // Inject current context into message headers
    Propagator.Inject(
        new PropagationContext(activity!.Context, Baggage.Current),
        props.Headers,
        (headers, key, value) => headers[key] = value);

    channel.BasicPublish("orders-exchange", "order.created", props, body);
}
```

### Service B — Consumer

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;
using OpenTelemetry;
using OpenTelemetry.Context.Propagation;
using RabbitMQ.Client.Events;

private static readonly ActivitySource Source = new("ServiceB.Messaging");
private static readonly TextMapPropagator Propagator = Propagators.DefaultTextMapPropagator;

public void HandleMessage(object? sender, BasicDeliverEventArgs ea)
{
    // Extract context from headers
    var parentContext = Propagator.Extract(
        default,
        ea.BasicProperties.Headers,
        (headers, key) =>
        {
            if (headers is null || !headers.TryGetValue(key, out var val))
                return [];
            // RabbitMQ stores header values as byte[]
            return [System.Text.Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])val)];
        });

    Baggage.Current = parentContext.Baggage;

    using var activity = Source.StartActivity(
        "OrderEvent receive",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext.ActivityContext);  // <-- links the trace

    // ... process the order
}
```

### OTel SDK registration (both services)

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("ServiceA.Messaging")   // or ServiceB.Messaging
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());
```

### Why this works

1. **`Propagator.Inject`** serialises `traceparent` / `tracestate` (W3C) into the message headers.
2. **`Propagator.Extract`** reads them back on the consumer side.
3. Passing `parentContext.ActivityContext` to `StartActivity` makes the consumer span a **child** of the producer span → one contiguous trace.

The byte[] → string cast in the extractor is required because RabbitMQ's .NET client stores header values as `byte[]`, not `string`.
